In this letter, President Barack Obama informs Congress about his designations of seven foreign individuals as appropriate for sanctions under the Foreign Narcotics Kingpin Designation Act. The individuals include Manuel Torres Felix and Gonzalo Inzunza Inzunza from Mexico, Haji Lal Jan Ishaqzai from Afghanistan, Kamchybek Asanbekovich Kolbayev from Kyrgyzstan, John Harun Mwau and Naima Mohamed Nyakiniywa from Kenya, and Javier Antonio Calle Serna from Colombia. The President directs sanctions against these individuals under the Act.